==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Boule
<hw>Bou"le</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A legislative council of elders
or chiefs; a senate.</def> <note>The <xex>boule</xex> of Homeric times
was an aristocratic body of princes and leaders, merely advisory to the
king. The Athenian <xex>boule</xex> of Solon's time was an elective
senate of 400, acting as a check on the popular <xex>ecclesia</xex>, for
which it examined and prepared bills for discussion. It later increased
to 500, chosen by lot, and extended its functions to embrace certain
matters of administration and oversight.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Legislature of modern Greece. See
<er>Legislature</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boulevard</ent>⟦br⟧
